
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes/relationships

class User {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
    +String email (username)
    +String password
    +String postalAddress
    +String phoneNumber
}

class Organizer {
    -List<Event> eventsOrganized
    -List<Attendee> attendeesInvited
    -List<Task> tasksCreated
}

class Attendee {
    -Event eventAttending
    -List<Task> attendeeTasks
    +ResponseStatus responseStatus
}

enum ResponseStatus {
    Attending
    Maybe
    NotAttending
}

class Event {
    -Date startTime
    -Date endTime
    +String occasion
    +Location location
    +String type
    -List<Organizer> organizers
    -List<Attendee> attendees
    -Checklist checklist
}

class Location {
    +String name
    +String address
}

class Checklist {
    -List<Task> tasks
}

class Task {
    +String description
    +TaskStatus status
    +Boolean isForAttendees
}

enum TaskStatus {
    NeedsToBeDone
    Done
    NotApplicable
}

' Inheritance relationships
User <|-- Organizer
User <|-- Attendee

' Association and aggregation relationships
Organizer "1" *-- "many" Event : organizes
Event "1" *-- "many" Organizer : has organizer(s)
Event "1" *-- "many" Attendee : invites
Attendee "1" *-- "1" Event : attends
Event "1" o-- "1" Checklist : has
Checklist "1" *-- "many" Task : contains
Organizer "1" *-- "many" Task : creates
Attendee "1" *-- "many" Task : selects
Event "1" *-- "1" Location : held at
Location "many" --> "many" Event : used in

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **User** is an abstract base class for both `Organizer` and `Attendee`.
- An **Organizer** can manage multiple **Events**.
- Each **Event** has a **Checklist**, which consists of **Tasks**.
- A **Task** can be assigned to **Attendees**; those who attend will see and select their assigned tasks.
- The **Location** and **Event Type** are reusable, so they are modeled as separate classes with potential reuse across multiple events.
- Enums (`ResponseStatus`, `TaskStatus`) are used to enforce valid statuses.

